<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Dominican Republic. Prov. Pedernales. On limestone terraces of maritime origin along both sides of the road to Pedernales, approx. 10 km southeast of Cabo Rojo, in dry forests dominated by large 
<taxonomicName authority="N.L.Britton &amp; J.N.Rose, 1920" authorityName="Britton &amp; Rose" authorityYear="1925" baseAuthorityName="DC." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cactaceae" genus="Dendrocereus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Dendrocereus undulosus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undulosus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Dendrocereus undulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
trees, 22 Dec. 1998, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Areces 6812</emphasis>
(Holotype: JBSD-n.v.; Isotypes: NY, HAJB, HNT-n.v.).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="17" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="17">
Although type material of 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. demissus" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" rank="species" species="demissus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">L. demissus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is reported to be at JBSD, HAJB, HNT, and NY (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2985/015.089.0303" author="Areces-Mallea, AE" journalOrPublisher="Cactus and Succulent Society Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="115 - 121" refId="B2" refString="Areces-Mallea, AE, 2017. Leptocereus demissus, a new species from southwestern Hispaniola. Cactus and Succulent Society Journal 89 (3): 115 - 121, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2985/015.089.0303" title="Leptocereus demissus, a new species from southwestern Hispaniola." url="https://doi.org/10.2985/015.089.0303" volume="89" year="2017">Areces-Mallea 2017</bibRefCitation>
), we have been unable to locate types at any of these institutions for comparative analysis for this work. Thus, we have based our knowledge on the morphological traits of this species using those characters given by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2985/015.089.0303" author="Areces-Mallea, AE" journalOrPublisher="Cactus and Succulent Society Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="17" pagination="115 - 121" refId="B2" refString="Areces-Mallea, AE, 2017. Leptocereus demissus, a new species from southwestern Hispaniola. Cactus and Succulent Society Journal 89 (3): 115 - 121, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2985/015.089.0303" title="Leptocereus demissus, a new species from southwestern Hispaniola." url="https://doi.org/10.2985/015.089.0303" volume="89" year="2017">Areces-Mallea (2017)</bibRefCitation>
, geography, and the one collection from near Oviedo made by us (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">Majure 5972</emphasis>
-see specimens examined; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Photographic plate of L. demissus A spiny fruit, and B slightly crenate stem of L. demissus (from Majure 5972). Photos by L. C. Majure." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.172.59497.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/502600" pageId="0" pageNumber="17">5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
